<subSubSection id="C34D3F8FC123FFBB2F61FC784968AD52" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE86C04C123FFBB2F61FC784968AD52" blockId="3.[114,1089,939,1220]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis id="B923B016C123FFBB2F61FC784B53AAD2" bold="true" box="[114,363,939,963]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Owing to the coloration of the pronotum, 
<taxonomicName id="4C571787C123FFBB2C37FC7F4943AAD2" authority="Bezděk &amp; Zhang, 2006" authorityName="Bezděk &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2006" box="[804,891,940,963]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B923B016C123FFBB2C37FC7F4943AAD2" box="[804,891,940,963]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">A. yangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2100D6DC123FFBB2C93FC7F49E9AAD2" box="[896,977,940,963]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles other 
<taxonomicName id="4C571787C123FFBB2FBEFC1F4B54AAF5" box="[173,364,972,996]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B923B016C123FFBB2FBEFC1F4B22AAF5" box="[173,282,972,996]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Apophylia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with extended black pattern on the pronotum – 
<taxonomicName id="4C571787C123FFBB2C48FC1F4AC4AD15" authority="(Fairmaire, 1888)" baseAuthorityName="Fairmaire" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandicornis">
<emphasis id="B923B016C123FFBB2C48FC1F49C7AAF5" box="[859,1023,972,996]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">A. grandicornis</emphasis>
(Fairmaire, 1888)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C571787C123FFBB2E16FC3F4838AD15" authority="Bezdek, 2003" authorityName="Bezdek" authorityYear="2003" box="[261,512,1004,1028]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frischi">
<emphasis id="B923B016C123FFBB2E16FC3F4B5EAD15" box="[261,358,1004,1028]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">A. frischi</emphasis>
Bezděk, 2003
</taxonomicName>
, and females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C571787C123FFBB2DB8FC3F49C3AD15" authority="Laboissiere, 1927" authorityName="Laboissiere" authorityYear="1927" box="[683,1019,1004,1028]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variicollis">
<emphasis id="B923B016C123FFBB2DB8FC3F490CAD15" box="[683,820,1004,1028]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">A. variicollis</emphasis>
Laboissière, 1927
</taxonomicName>
. However, all these species have a yellow anterior part of the head (completely black in 
<taxonomicName id="4C571787C123FFBB2CD5FBDF4E25AD32" authority="Bezděk &amp; Zhang, 2006" authorityName="Bezděk &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2006" box="[966,1053,1036,1059]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B923B016C123FFBB2CD5FBDF4E25AD32" box="[966,1053,1036,1059]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">A. yangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2100D6DC123FFBB2B31FBDF4A9AAD55" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), at least partly yellow legs, and a dull or semiopaque pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34D3F8FC123FFBB2F61FB9F4B5BADB5" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE86C04C123FFBB2F61FB9F4BE2AD95" blockId="3.[114,1089,939,1220]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis id="B923B016C123FFBB2F61FB9F4ACAAD75" bold="true" box="[114,242,1100,1124]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is dedicated to Prof. Xing-ke Yang (
<collectingCountry id="F3402C94C123FFBB2C1BFB9F4974AD75" box="[776,844,1100,1124]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4993A2E6C123FFBB2C4BFB9F4993AD75" box="[856,939,1100,1124]" country="China" name="Beijing" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Beijing</collectingRegion>
), an excellent specialist in Chinese Galerucinae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE86C04C123FFBB2F61FB584B5BADB5" blockId="3.[114,1089,939,1220]" box="[114,355,1163,1188]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis id="B923B016C123FFBB2F61FB584AD7ADB2" bold="true" box="[114,239,1163,1187]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Bionomics.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
